Jennifer Barnett worked at Archway School in Stroud between 1980 and 1997 . 
  She left teaching to have her fourth child but was diagnosed with mesothelioma . 
  The 60-year-old died last September 14 months after being diagnosed with lung cancer . 
  Her husband said she was exposed to asbestos while working on a farm . 
  He is now taking legal action against Gloucestershire County Council . 
  Mrs Barnett worked as an art teacher and hung pupils' work on walls lined with asbestos . 
  She worked at the school for 17 years before her death . 
 